
## Sample Noisy Trap Function

This shows the statistical model behind each n-tuple after running it
for a sample budget of 5,000 on a simple trap function.  There are
five parameters (hence 5 dimensions of the search space).  The sample
problem is a generalised version of Noisy OneMax.  Each parameter can
take four possible values (hence indices go from 0 .. 3).  The fitness
of each point is the sum of the indices (but with a trap) plus Gaussian noise with zero
mean and standard deviation of 1.0.  The trap function is that if all 5 parameters
have their maximum value of 3 then the noise-free fitness is 0.0.


## Output explained:


First we have the 5 1-tuples (1 for each of the 5 dimensions)

Then we have the 5*4/2 = 10  (1 for each distinct pair)

And finally the single 5-tuple.

For each row we have the parameter value indices followed by the number of
times it was sampled, the mean value and the standard deviation (which will be Nan if
there are fewer than two samples).
